I’m going to call these ‘everything but the kitchen sink’ triple chocolate bliss balls🚰 because I put legitimately everything I could think of in them 😂 My sweet tooth has been out of this world lately, so we’ll see how long these last 🤔🤷🏽‍♀️ Try it — 3/4C @purely_elizabeth ancient grain oats, 3Tbsp flaxseed, 1/4C crushed cashews (blended in food processor), 1 scoop @vitalproteins collagen peptides, 1 Tbsp @navitasorganics cacao powder, 1Tbsp @navitasorganics chopped cacao nibs, 2Tbsp each of melted @nutiva coconut oil, @nutiva coconut butter, @califiafarms unsweetened vanilla almond milk & @wegmans cashew butter, 1Tbsp each of @nutiva MCT oil, @365bywholefoods cinnamon & pure maple syrup. Roll into balls & dust with crushed @lovegrown comet crispies. Refrigerate for 1 hour...if you can wait that long.

Behold!!!! a greek [sneak] peak at one of the many meal prep recipes comin your way v v soon 😏
What went down - Organic ground turkey, spinach, feta, 2 eggs, and gluten free bread crumbs rolled into meatballs (or patty’s if that’s more your style). Bake in the oven on 425 for ~14 minutes. Throw them over a bed of chopped romaine with a simple Greek vegetable medley (mines chopped tomatoes, cucumber, parsley, salt & pepper) and boom - brown bag lunch just got E X T R A. Top it off with tzatziki sauce for my favorite Greek Meatball Lunch Bowl.

Happy earth day from me and the crunchy chickpea kale salad you’ll want to make for lunch this week 🌎
.
.
Preheat oven to 400. Drain chickpeas and pat dry with paper towel. Spray with @chosenfoods Avocado oil and season with garlic & chili powder. Bake in the oven for roughly 40 minutes (I like them super crunchy and even a little burnt) mixing them up occasionally with a spatula. Take them out of the oven and let them cool entirely (this keeps them crunchy when storing the rest in the fridge). I served mine over baby kale and arugula mix, shredded Parmesan, grape tomatoes & @wegmans Yogurt Caesar dressing.

Finally perfected a homemade pumpkin spice latte and OH MY GOURD it’s delicious.
Drankkkkkk: over medium-low heat, warm 1/2 cup of @thenewbarn barista blend almond milk. Add 2-3 tablespoons of @wholefoods organic pumpkin purée, a dash of ground ginger, & @365bywholefoods organic pumpkin pie spice. Stir until creamy & pour into your blender. Add 8 ounces of hot coffee, 1tsp @foursigmatic lions mane (optional), 1tsp @nutiva MCT oil, 1 scoop of @vitalproteins collagen peptides, (this makes it frothy!!) a tiny bit of pure maple syrup and blend 🌪 top with cinnamon, take a pic, & embrace the basic.

Need a protein packed last minute dinner recipe?! I gotchu 😏
— LEMON HONEY CHICKEN SAUSAGE PASTA SALAD —
Cook one package of @eatbanza chickpea pasta el dente and immediately rinse in cold water. Strain completely and set aside.
Chop up @wegmans organic caprese chicken sausage and cook in @chosenfoods avocado oil over medium heat. Once chicken sausage is almost done cooking, add in sun dried tomatoes and frozen peas and continue cooking. Combine pasta and a few handfuls of fresh spinach to a mixing bowl and add chicken sausage, sun dried tomatoes and peas once cooled. Top with homemade lemon honey dressing ( I used the juice of 1 lemon, 1/2 tsp raw honey, 1/2 tsp olive oil, sat & pepper), shredded parmesan & chopped scallions 🤤

low maintenance Sunday brunch, anyone? 🍳 this one pan crispy kale, sweet potato & turkey bacon hash was one for the books 📖 deets 👇🏼
.
.
.
In medium cast iron skillet cook two slices of @applegate turkey bacon over medium heat and set aside. Spray pan with a generous amount of @chosenfoods avocado oil then place chopped Jersey white sweet potatoes, red onion and a handful of chopped kale into the pan. Season with pink salt, pepper, and red pepper flakes. Once sweet potatoes start to get brown and crispy, create a hole in the middle of the pan by pushing the cooked hash to the sides, crack an egg, and let cook. Once the egg is cooked to your liking, chop up the turkey bacon and add to the skillet!

My typical response to salad in the winter (or usually in general) = KALE NO. Even though I like eating healthy, if I’m between a burger and a salad, burger wins every time. But this recipe was actually really freaking good. And unpopular opinion ... I actually thoroughly enjoy consuming kale 🤷🏽‍♀️ especially in this sweet & spicy kale salad 👏🏼
Details:
1. Chop kale & sweet potatoes nice and small
2. Preheat oven to 425 and roast sweet potatoes & chickpeas in avocado oil, pink salt, pepper, paprika, & chili powder for 20-25 min.
3. Deseed a pomegranate while sweet potatoes and chickpeas are cooking.
4. Dress kale in a little bit of yogurt balsamic dressing & add in chickpeas, sweet potato & pomegranate! ** I ate this for lunch so it was the perfect amount of food, but if you want a heavier meal, add red quinoa (that’s what I’m doing tonight for dinner).
